HEADWORD: factotum
<hw>fac*to"tum</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧k*t⟦omac⟧"t⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>factotums</plw> <pr>(-t⟦ucr⟧mz)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L., do everything; <ets>facere</ets> to do + <ets>totus</ets> all
: cf. F. <ets>factotum</ets>. See <er>Fact</er>, and
<er>Total</er>.]</ety> <def>A person employed to do all kinds of work or
business; a person with many different responsibilities.</def>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>factual</ent>⟦br⟧
